{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccwdtw1waXFkojnHWjFEt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DmXP9R3W91AywP5cgxUhGA","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r1/memory/project_ci_flaky_test_fix.md","content":"---\nname: ci-flaky-test-fix\ndescription: Intermittent CI test failure was a race condition in fixture setup, fixed with a lock around a shared file\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure took a full afternoon to diagnose (2026-07-11). Root cause: a race condition in test fixture setup — multiple tests/processes writing to a shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around access to that shared file.\n\n**Why:** Without the lock, fixture setup could interleave across tests, causing nondeterministic failures that were hard to reproduce.\n\n**How to apply:** If similar intermittent/flaky CI failures show up later in this project, check fixture setup for shared-resource races first. Don't remove or \"simplify away\" locking around shared fixture files without understanding this history — it's there to prevent the exact race condition described above.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":560,"cache_read_input_tokens":32542,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":560},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28486111-fc83-4052-b72d-6971c9cb8118","uuid":"3782f92a-ca0e-496a-aeb7-dee828d5ed8e","request_id":"req_011CcwdtuwwurNqmt6WEhZxG"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DmXP9R3W91AywP5cgxUhGA","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r1/memory/project_ci_flaky_test_fix.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28486111-fc83-4052-b72d-6971c9cb8118","uuid":"ae404c0f-b844-40fd-8a0b-7b274a67e1e9","timestamp":"2026-07-12T05:48:04.923Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r1/memory/project_ci_flaky_test_fix.md","content":"---\nname: ci-flaky-test-fix\ndescription: \"Intermittent CI test failure was a race condition in fixture setup, fixed with a lock around a shared file\"\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: 28486111-fc83-4052-b72d-6971c9cb8118\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure took a full afternoon to diagnose (2026-07-11). Root cause: a race condition in test fixture setup — multiple tests/processes writing to a shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around access to that shared file.\n\n**Why:** Without the lock, fixture setup could interleave across tests, causing nondeterministic failures that were hard to reproduce.\n\n**How to apply:** If similar intermittent/flaky CI failures show up later in this project, check fixture setup for shared-resource races first. Don't remove or \"simplify away\" locking around shared fixture files without understanding this history — it's there to prevent the exact race condition described above.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
